{"id":136,"ayahs":[{"number":69,"arabic":"وَمَا عَلَى ٱلَّذِينَ يَتَّقُونَ مِنْ حِسَابِهِم مِّن شَىْءٍۢ وَلَٰكِن ذِكْرَىٰ لَعَلَّهُمْ يَتَّقُونَ","translation":"for whom those who are conscious of God are in no wise accountable. Theirs, however, is the duty to admonish [the sinners], so that they might become conscious of God.","audio":"https://cdn.islamic.network/quran/audio/128/ar.alafasy/858.mp3","surahId":6,"words":[{"id":59284,"position":1,"arabic":"وَمَا","translation":"এবং নেই (দায়িত্ব)","audioUrl":"wbw/006_069_001.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":59285,"position":2,"arabic":"عَلَى","translation":"উপর","audioUrl":"wbw/006_069_002.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":59286,"position":3,"arabic":"ٱلَّذِينَ","translation":"(তাদের) যারা","audioUrl":"wbw/006_069_003.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":59287,"position":4,"arabic":"يَتَّقُونَ","translation":"ভয় করে","audioUrl":"wbw/006_069_004.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":59288,"position":5,"arabic":"مِنْ","translation":"থেকে","audioUrl":"wbw/006_069_005.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":59289,"position":6,"arabic":"حِسَابِهِم","translation":"হিসাবের তাদের","audioUrl":"wbw/006_069_006.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":59290,"position":7,"arabic":"مِّن","translation":"কোনো","audioUrl":"wbw/006_069_007.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":59291,"position":8,"arabic":"شَىْءٍۢ","translation":"কিছুই","audioUrl":"wbw/006_069_008.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":59292,"position":9,"arabic":"وَلَـٰكِن","translation":"কিন্তু","audioUrl":"wbw/006_069_009.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":59293,"position":10,"arabic":"ذِكْرَىٰ","translation":"উপদেশের (দায়িত্ব আছে)","audioUrl":"wbw/006_069_010.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":59294,"position":11,"arabic":"لَعَلَّهُمْ","translation":"যাতে তারা","audioUrl":"wbw/006_069_011.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":59295,"position":12,"arabic":"يَتَّقُونَ","translation":"বিরত থাকে","audioUrl":"wbw/006_069_012.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":59296,"position":13,"arabic":"٦٩","translation":"(৬৯)","audioUrl":null,"charTypeName":"end"}]},{"number":70,"arabic":"وَذَرِ ٱلَّذِينَ ٱتَّخَذُوا۟ دِينَهُمْ لَعِبًۭا وَلَهْوًۭا وَغَرَّتْهُمُ ٱلْحَيَوٰةُ ٱلدُّنْيَا ۚ وَذَكِّرْ بِهِۦٓ أَن تُبْسَلَ نَفْسٌۢ بِمَا كَسَبَتْ لَيْسَ لَهَا مِن دُونِ ٱللَّهِ وَلِىٌّۭ وَلَا شَفِيعٌۭ وَإِن تَعْدِلْ كُلَّ عَدْلٍۢ لَّا يُؤْخَذْ مِنْهَآ ۗ أُو۟لَٰٓئِكَ ٱلَّذِينَ أُبْسِلُوا۟ بِمَا كَسَبُوا۟ ۖ لَهُمْ شَرَابٌۭ مِّنْ حَمِيمٍۢ وَعَذَابٌ أَلِيمٌۢ بِمَا كَانُوا۟ يَكْفُرُونَ","translation":"And leave to themselves all those who, beguiled by the life of this world, have made play and passing delights their religion; but remind [them] herewith that [in the life to come] every human being shall be held in pledge for whatever wrong he has done, and shall have none to protect him from God, and none to intercede for him; and though he offer any conceivable ransom, it shall not be accepted from him. It is [people such as] these that shall be held in pledge for the wrong they have done; for them there is [in the life to come] a draught of burning despair and grievous suffering awaits them because of their persistent refusal to acknowledge the truth.","audio":"https://cdn.islamic.network/quran/audio/128/ar.alafasy/859.mp3","surahId":6,"words":[{"id":59469,"position":1,"arabic":"وَذَرِ","translation":"এবং ছেড়ে দাও","audioUrl":"wbw/006_070_001.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":59470,"position":2,"arabic":"ٱلَّذِينَ","translation":"(তাদেরকে) যারা","audioUrl":"wbw/006_070_002.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":59471,"position":3,"arabic":"ٱتَّخَذُوا۟","translation":"গ্রহণ করেছে","audioUrl":"wbw/006_070_003.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":59472,"position":4,"arabic":"دِينَهُمْ","translation":"দীনকে তাদের","audioUrl":"wbw/006_070_004.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":59473,"position":5,"arabic":"لَعِبًۭا","translation":"ক্রীড়া","audioUrl":"wbw/006_070_005.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":59474,"position":6,"arabic":"وَلَهْوًۭا","translation":"ও কৌতুকরূপে","audioUrl":"wbw/006_070_006.mp3","ch